    "description": "Yushin Company engages in the development, production, sale, and maintenance of Cartesian robots and other industrial equipment and systems for factory automation in Japan and internationally. It offers take out robots, including multi-function, swing type take-out, side entry, horizontal molding, vertical molding machine, and sprue picker robots; palletizing robots for injection-molded products and peripheral equipment; end-of-arm tools; stock systems comprising stockers and conveyors; and downstream equipment, such as gate cut system, assembly, and insert workpiece feeder, as well as labor-saving automation equipment. The company also provides custom-ordered equipment; and parts and maintenance services. The company was formerly known as Yushin Precision Equipment Co., Ltd. and changed its name to Yushin Company in April 2025. Yushin Company was founded in 1971 and is headquartered in Kyoto, Japan."
